import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_json('normal-2d.json')

# Plot scatter plot
sns.scatterplot(x='X', y='Y', data=data)

# Set chart title
plt.title('What is the correlation between X and Y?', wrap=True)

# Return plot object
plt.show()
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_json('normal-2d.json')

# Plot histogram of X
sns.histplot(data=data, x='X', color='blue', kde=True)
plt.axvline(data['X'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['X'].mean():.2f}")
plt.legend()
plt.title('What is the distribution of X?')
plt.xlabel('X')
plt.ylabel('Frequency')

# Show plot
plt.show()
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_json('normal-2d.json')

# Plot histogram of Y
sns.histplot(data=data, x='Y', color='blue', kde=True)
plt.axvline(data['Y'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean = {:.2f}'.format(data['Y'].mean()))
plt.legend()
plt.title('What is the distribution of Y?')
plt.xlabel('Y')
plt.ylabel('Frequency')

plt.show()

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_json('normal-2d.json')

# Convert date fields to date types
data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')

# Drop rows with NaT values
data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

# Set chart style
sns.set_style("darkgrid")

# Create line chart
sns.lineplot(x='date', y='Y', data=data, color='blue', label='Y')
sns.lineplot(x='date', y='X', data=data, color='red', label='X')

# Set chart title and axis labels
plt.title('What is the relationship between X and Y over time?', wrap=True)
plt.xlabel('Date')
plt.ylabel('Value')

# Rotate x-axis labels for legibility
plt.xticks(rotation=45)

# Add legend
plt.legend()

# Show plot
plt.show()
```
